<p>The tricky thing here is the column definition will be modified to whatever you put in your <code>MODIFY</code> statement, so if my <code>product</code>.<code>name</code> column above was <code>NOT NULL</code>, after running the statements above, it will become nullable. To make it easy I have written a <a href="https://gist.github.com/solidfoxrock/9849810">PHP script</a> to do this job. The script will generate all these <code>ALTER TABLE MODIFY</code> queries for you. The generated queries preserve your existing column definitions by reading them from <code>SHOW CREATE TABLE</code>. Please let me know if you have any problems running this script.</p>
